Dating: 3RD INTERMEDIATE PERIOD (not before); LATE PERIOD; GRAECO-ROMAN PERIOD (not after)
Name: Alabaster vase
Description: Vase in the form of a long oval with very thin walls.  Short distinct neck, ring-shaped rim and concave unstable base.The upper part of the body has two symmetrically placed appendages for handles. They are rectangular in cross-section.
